<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521367>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Caenis marataoan sp. nov. female imago:A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, habitus, ventral view. (Scale: Figs 3A–C = 0.5 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6521367/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521365>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Caenis marataoan sp. nov. male imago, genitalia: A, ventral view; B–E, variations in forceps. Abbreviations: f = forceps; p = penis; sp = styliger plate; a = apophysis; cs = central sclerite. (Scale: Fig. 2A = 0.1 mm; Figs 2B–E = 0.05 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6521365/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521369>
    dc:description "FIGURE. 5. Caenis marataoan sp. nov. egg: A, general view; B, detail of micropyle; C, detail of polar cap. Abbreviations: pc = polar cap; c = chorion; mc = micropyle; sg = sperm guide. (Scale: Fig. 4A = 20 µm; Figs 4B, C = 10 µm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6521369/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521371>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Male imagos, body dorsal view and genitalia ventral view: A–B, Brasilocaenis irmleri; C–D, B. elidioi; E–F, Caenis chamie; G–H, C. fittkaui. (Scale: Figs 5A, C, E, F = 1 mm; Figs 5B, D, F, H = 0.2 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6521371/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521363>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Caenis marataoan sp. nov. male imago: A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, habitus, ventral view; D, detail of thorax (ventral view); E, detail of abdomen (dorsal view). (Scale: Figs 1A–E = 0.5 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6521363/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521361>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Distributional map with records of Brasilocaenis irmleri, B. elidioi, Caenis chamie, C. fittkaui, and Caenis marataoan sp. nov. A, Map of South America indicating previous records; B, Map of Piauí State, Brazil with new distributional records." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6521361/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

